<body id="controller___installation">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">Controller - Installation</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Installation of the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">CX9020 controller</span></em>. The <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">CX9020 controller</span></em> must be installed onto the mounting rail
        located in the slots 20 and 21 in the <em class="ph i">Upmast Cabinet</em>. The mounting rail is located at
        the very top right side of the <em class="ph i">Upmast Cabinet</em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Position the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">CX9020 controller</span></em> on the mounting
                    rail.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Push it slightly until it engages on the right-hand side. This is indicated by
                    a distinct click (see <a class="xref" href="#controller___installation__CPU_Installation">Figure 1</a>).</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="controller___installation__CPU_Installation"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 1. </span>Installation of the CPU onto the rail</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-03040107A-A-D2714-06390-A-A-1.jpg" />
                    </div>

                
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Insert the bar clips on the top side and underside.</span>
                <div class="itemgroup stepresult">The bars are then engaged again. The engagement of the individual bars
                    is indicated by a distinct click.</div>
            </li>
<li class="li step stepexpand">
                <span class="ph cmd">Once the <em class="ph i">CPU</em> and <em class="ph i">Power Supply Converter</em> are mounted, ensure the
                    correct cables are connected to the corresponding power terminals (see <a class="xref" href="#controller___installation__24V_CX9020_Controller">Figure 2</a>).</span>
                
                    <div class="fig fignone" id="controller___installation__24V_CX9020_Controller"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 2. </span>24V CX9020 Controller</span>
                        
                        <img class="image" src="../images/Controller_CX9020.png" height="288" width="492" />
                        <dl class="dl">
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">1</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Ethernet und USB connection</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">2</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">DVI connection</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">3</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Multi optional interface (e.g. RS232, Profibus, CANopen)</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">4</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Status LEDs</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">5</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">Battery compartment (behind the flap)</dd>

                            
                            
                                <dt class="dt dlterm">6</dt>

                                <dd class="dd">2 x MicroSD</dd>

                            
                        </dl>

                    </div>

                
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

